<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Garth S. McAlister, Barrister and Solicitor, of 203-1807 Fir Street, Vancouver, British Columbia make oath and say as follows:</P>
<P>1. I am counsel for the Appellant, Jameson House Ventures Ltd. in this appeal. As such I have personal knowledge of the matters hereinafter deposed to, save and except where the same are stated to be on information and belief and where so stated I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<P>2. I swear this affidavit in support of an application for an order that this Appeal be heard and determined by the same division of this Court as the following two Appeals:
<P1>a. Court of Appeal File No. CA44250 between The Owners, Strata Plan LMS3905 as Respondent and Crystal Square Parking Corporation as Appellant (the &ldquo;Crystal Square Appeal&rdquo;), and</P1>
<P1>b. Court of Appeal File No. File No. CA44684between The Owners, Strata Plan NWS 3457 as Appellant and The Owners, Strata Plan LMS 1425 as Respondent (the &ldquo;Scottsdale Village Appeal&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>I will refer to this Appeal, the Crystal Square Appeal in the Scottsdale Village Appeal collectively as the &ldquo;Three Appeals&rdquo;.</P1></P>
<P>3. The status of this Appeal is as follows:
<P1>a. The Notice of Appeal was filed on November 16, 2017;</P1>
<P1>b. A Notice of Appearance was filed on November 17, 2017;</P1>
<P1>c. The Appeal Record was filed on January 12, 2018;</P1>
<P1>d. Joint Appeal Books are in the process of being finalized and will be filed shortly.</P1></P>
<P>4. I am informed by Emily Kirkpatrick, who is one of the counsel for the Appellant in the Crystal Square Appeal, that the status of the Crystal Square Appeal is as follows:
<P1>a. The Notice of Appeal was filed on February 15, 2017;</P1>
<P1>b. The Notice of Appearance was filed on February 16, 2017;</P1>
<P1>c. The Appellant filed its factum on July 12, 2017;</P1>
<P1>d. The Respondent filed its factum on September 11, 2017;</P1>
<P1>e. No date has yet been set for the hearing of this appeal.</P1></P>
<P>5. I am informed by James Klassen, who is counsel for the Respondent in the Scottsdale Village Appeal, that the status of the Scottsdale Village Appeal is as follows:
<P1>a. The Notice of Appeal was filed on August 22, 2017;</P1>
<P1>b. The Notice of Appearance was filed on September 1, 2017;</P1>
<P1>c. No Appeal Record has been filed, nor have Appeal Books been filed.</P1></P>
<P>6. I am informed by Stephen Hamilton, who is counsel for the Respondent in the Crystal Square Appeal and for the Appellant in the Scottsdale Village Appeal that he will not be continuing as counsel for the Appellant in the Scottsdale Village Appeal and that the Appellant in that appeal is looking to retain other counsel.</P>
<P>7. Now produced and shown to me:
<P1>a. As <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the factum filed on behalf of the Appellant in the Crystal Square Appeal;</P1>
<P1>b. As <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the Reasons for Judgement of Madam Justice Donegan pronounced November 2, 2017 in relation to this Appeal;</P1>
<P1>c. As <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the Reasons for Judgement of Madam Justice Young pronounced January 17, 2017 in relation to the Crystal Square Appeal;</P1>
<P1>d. As <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD> is a copy of the Reasons for Judgement of Mr. Justice Branch pronounced August 2, 2017 in relation to the Scottsdale Village Appeal.</P1></P>
<P>8. It is apparent from the Reasons for Judgment underlying each of the three Appeals that a legal conclusion common to all three is that courts in Canada, and in particular courts in British Columbia, do not recognize exceptions to the general rule that positive covenants do not run with the land.</P>
<P>9. That legal conclusion is directly challenged by the Appellant as a ground of appeal in the Crystal Square Appeal, and a similar challenge will be one of the grounds of appeal in this Appeal. It is my understanding, although I am not sure, that such a challenge will also be a ground of appeal in the Scottsdale Village Appeal.</P>
<P>10. I swear this affidavit in support of an application that the Three Appeals be heard and determined by the same division of this Court (the &ldquo;Order Sought&rdquo;).</P>
<P>11. There have been discussions between the lawyers for the parties in all Three Appeals about them being heard and determined by the same division of this Court and, for the purposes of this application, I have communicated with each of them asking whether their respective clients would be prepared to consent to the Order Sought.</P>
<P>12. I am informed by:
<P1>a. Alex Chang, who is one of the counsel representing the Respondent in this Appeal, that the Respondent consents to the Order Sought;</P1>
<P1>b. Stephen Hamilton that:
<P2>i. As counsel for the Respondent in the Crystal Square Appeal, the Respondent in that appeal consents to the Order Sought;</P2>
<P2>ii. He does not have instructions to consent to the Order Sought on behalf of the Appellant in the Scottsdale Village Appeal because he will not be continuing as counsel in that appeal;</P2></P1>
<P1>c. Emily Fitzpatrick, who is one of the counsel representing the Appellant in the Crystal Square Appeal, that the Order Sought &ldquo;makes sense&rdquo;.</P1></P>
<P>13. I have asked for but not yet received the consent to the Order Sought from James Klassen, who is counsel for the Respondent in the Scottsdale Village Appeal.</P>
<P>14. In addition to serving the Respondent in this appeal, we will be serving the application materials on the parties to the Crystal Square and the Scottsdale Village Appeals and, if the Court grants the Order Sought, we will also be asking the Court to order that a consent order to the same effect as the Order Sought may be filed in each of the Crystal Square Appeal and the Scottsdale Village Appeal.</P>
